<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - Meritor Transfer Cases MTC-4208, -4210, and -4213 -
        Assembly - Shim Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Shim Assembly</title>
        <para>In order to adjust end play on any shaft, it is necessary to split the transfer case.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the transfer case in the stand so that the rear cover is facing UP. Remove the
                case-to-cover capscrews.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable lift to remove the rear cover. Mount the cover so that the pressed-in bearing
                cups can be removed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a bearing puller to remove the bearing cups from the cover. Shims are placed between the
                cover and the cup. Refer to the Figures at the beginning of this manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select the correct shim or shims to achieve the correct end play. If the end play
                measurement is below 0.001-inch (0.03 mm), which indicates a pre-loaded shaft, start by removing shims
                until some measurable end play is observed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <table id="t1303501">
            <title>Example of Shim Selection</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.01*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.99*"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Initial measurement (idler shaft)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>0.018-inch (0.46 mm)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Specification</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>0.001-to 0.005-inch (0.03-0.13 mm)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Required shim stack</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>0.017- to 0.013-inch (0.43-0.33 mm)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
