                            <para>2 (0.005)</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="underscr">1 (0.003)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>0.013-inch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1 (0.010)</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="underscr">2 (0.003)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>0.016-inch</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1 (0.25 mm)</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="underscr">1 (0.13 mm)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>0.38 mm</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>2 (0.13 mm)</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="underscr">1 (0.08 mm)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>0.34 mm</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1 (0.25 mm)</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="underscr">2 (0.08 mm)</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>0.41 mm</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After selecting the correct shim combination, place the shims in the bottom of the bearing
                bore. Refer to the Figures at the beginning of this manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the bearing cup into the bore until it is completely seated. The shims must be
                centered in the bore while pressing in the bearing cup.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat Steps 3-6 for each bearing needing an end play adjustment.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before final assembly, verify that each shim selection procedure results in the correct end play
                    specification. Repeat the end play measurement steps, as necessary, to obtain the correct end play
                    specification on all shafts.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reassemble the cover to the case. Install at least six case-to-cover capscrews.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
